                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "# Frontier Military Verification Bot - Hackathon POC\n\nPerfect! I understand the vision. Let me help you build a **fast, focused military verification bot** for your hackathon. Here's a comprehensive implementation plan:\n\n---\n\n## üéØ **Core Objectives**\n\n1. **Fast verification** - Name matching as primary verification\n2. **Document validity** - Check expiration dates\n3. **Graceful failures** - Human escalation path when bot can't verify\n4. **Seamless UX** - Integrated into existing MyFrontier app flow\n\n---\n\n## üèóÔ∏è **Technical Architecture**\n\n### **Tech Stack Recommendation**\n\n```\nFrontend: React Native (existing MyFrontier app)\nBackend: Python Flask/FastAPI\nOCR Engine: Tesseract OCR + Google Cloud Vision API (fallback)\nName Matching: FuzzyWuzzy + RapidFuzz\nDocument Classification: OpenCV + Custom ML model\nDatabase: PostgreSQL\nFile Storage: AWS S3\n```\n\n---\n\n## üìã **Acceptable Military Documents**\n\n### **Primary Documents (Highest Confidence)**\n1. **Common Access Card (CAC)** - Active duty\n2. **Department of Defense ID Card** - Active/Reserve/Guard\n3. **Veteran Health ID Card (VHIC)**\n4. **Uniformed Services ID Card** - Retirees\n5. **VA Medical Center ID Card**\n\n### **Secondary Documents (Supporting)**\n6. **DD Form 214** - Certificate of Release/Discharge\n7. **DD Form 215** - Correction to DD214\n8. **NGB Form 22** - National Guard Report of Separation\n9. **Veterans Affairs Award Letter**\n10. **Military Orders/Assignment Orders**\n\n### **Tertiary Documents (May require additional verification)**\n11. **Military driver's license**\n12. **LES (Leave and Earnings Statement)**\n13. **Veteran Organization membership cards** (VFW, American Legion)\n\n---\n\n## ü§ñ **Bot Implementation**\n\n### **Step 1: Document Upload Portal**\n\n```python\n# Frontend Component (React Native)\nimport React, { useState } from 'react';\nimport { View, Text, TouchableOpacity, Image } from 'react-native';\nimport DocumentPicker from 'react-native-document-picker';\nimport ImagePicker from 'react-native-image-crop-picker';\n\nconst MilitaryVerificationPortal = ({ accountHolder, accountNumber }) => {\n  const [uploadedDoc, setUploadedDoc] = useState(null);\n  const [verificationStatus, setVerificationStatus] = useState('idle');\n\n  const handleDocumentUpload = async () => {\n    try {\n      const result = await DocumentPicker.pick({\n        type: [DocumentPicker.types.images, DocumentPicker.types.pdf],\n      });\n      \n      setUploadedDoc(result);\n      processDocument(result);\n    } catch (err) {\n      if (DocumentPicker.isCancel(err)) {\n        // User cancelled\n      } else {\n        throw err;\n      }\n    }\n  };\n\n  const handleCameraCapture = async () => {\n    const image = await ImagePicker.openCamera({\n      width: 1200,\n      height: 800,\n      cropping: true,\n      includeBase64: true,\n    });\n    \n    processDocument(image);\n  };\n\n  const processDocument = async (doc) => {\n    setVerificationStatus('processing');\n    \n    const formData = new FormData();\n    formData.append('document', doc);\n    formData.append('account_holder', accountHolder);\n    formData.append('account_number', accountNumber);\n\n    try {\n      const response = await fetch('https://api.frontier.com/verify/military', {\n        method: 'POST',\n        body: formData,\n        headers: {\n          'Authorization': `Bearer ${userToken}`,\n        },\n      });\n\n      const result = await response.json();\n      setVerificationStatus(result.status);\n      \n      if (result.verified) {\n        // Show success message and benefits\n        navigateToSuccessScreen(result);\n      } else {\n        // Show escalation options\n        navigateToSupportScreen(result);\n      }\n    } catch (error) {\n      setVerificationStatus('error');\n    }\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <View style={styles.container}>\n      <Text style={styles.title}>Military Verification</Text>\n      <Text style={styles.subtitle}>\n        Upload your military ID or discharge papers\n      </Text>\n\n      <TouchableOpacity \n        style={styles.uploadButton} \n        onPress={handleCameraCapture}\n      >\n        <Text>üì∑ Take Photo of ID</Text>\n      </TouchableOpacity>\n\n      <TouchableOpacity \n        style={styles.uploadButton} \n        onPress={handleDocumentUpload}\n      >\n        <Text>üìÅ Upload Document</Text>\n      </TouchableOpacity>\n\n      {verificationStatus === 'processing' && (\n        <View style={styles.processingView}>\n          <ActivityIndicator size=\"large\" />\n          <Text>Verifying your documents...</Text>\n        </View>\n      )}\n    </View>\n  );\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Step 2: Backend Verification Engine**\n\n```python\n# app.py - Flask Backend\nfrom flask import Flask, request, jsonify\nfrom werkzeug.utils import secure_filename\nimport cv2\nimport pytesseract\nfrom PIL import Image\nimport numpy as np\nfrom fuzzywuzzy import fuzz\nfrom datetime import datetime\nimport re\nimport os\n\napp = Flask(__name__)\n\nclass MilitaryVerificationBot:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.confidence_threshold = 85  # Name match threshold\n        self.supported_formats = ['jpg', 'jpeg', 'png', 'pdf']\n        \n    def preprocess_image(self, image_path):\n        \"\"\"Enhance image quality for better OCR\"\"\"\n        img = cv2.imread(image_path)\n        \n        # Convert to grayscale\n        gray = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)\n        \n        # Apply thresholding\n        thresh = cv2.threshold(gray, 0, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY + cv2.THRESH_OTSU)[1]\n        \n        # Denoise\n        denoised = cv2.fastNlMeansDenoising(thresh)\n        \n        # Increase contrast\n        clahe = cv2.createCLAHE(clipLimit=2.0, tileGridSize=(8,8))\n        enhanced = clahe.apply(denoised)\n        \n        return enhanced\n    \n    def extract_text_from_image(self, image_path):\n        \"\"\"Extract text using OCR\"\"\"\n        # Preprocess\n        processed_img = self.preprocess_image(image_path)\n        \n        # OCR with custom config\n        custom_config = r'--oem 3 --psm 6'\n        text = pytesseract.image_to_string(processed_img, config=custom_config)\n        \n        return text\n    \n    def classify_document_type(self, text):\n        \"\"\"Identify what type of military document this is\"\"\"\n        text_lower = text.lower()\n        \n        document_types = {\n            'CAC': ['common access card', 'cac', 'department of defense'],\n            'DD214': ['dd214', 'dd 214', 'certificate of release', 'discharge'],\n            'VHIC': ['veteran health', 'vhic', 'veterans health'],\n            'RETIREE_ID': ['uniformed services', 'retiree', 'retired'],\n            'VA_CARD': ['veterans affairs', 'department of veterans'],\n            'ORDERS': ['orders', 'reporting date', 'duty station']\n        }\n        \n        for doc_type, keywords in document_types.items():\n            if any(keyword in text_lower for keyword in keywords):\n                return doc_type\n        \n        return 'UNKNOWN'\n    \n    def extract_name_from_document(self, text, doc_type):\n        \"\"\"Extract name based on document type patterns\"\"\"\n        lines = text.split('\\n')\n        \n        # Common patterns for name extraction\n        name_patterns = [\n            r'NAME[:\\s]+([A-Z][A-Z\\s]+)',\n            r'LAST[,\\s]+FIRST[,\\s]+MIDDLE[:\\s]+([A-Z\\s,]+)',\n            r'([A-Z]+)[,\\s]+([A-Z]+)[,\\s]*([A-Z]*)',\n        ]\n        \n        potential_names = []\n        \n        for line in lines:\n            for pattern in name_patterns:\n                match = re.search(pattern, line, re.IGNORECASE)\n                if match:\n                    potential_names.append(match.group(1).strip())\n        \n        # Also look for standalone capital letter sequences (likely names)\n        for line in lines:\n            words = line.split()\n            if len(words) >= 2:\n                if all(word[0].isupper() for word in words if len(word) > 1):\n                    potential_names.append(line.strip())\n        \n        return potential_names\n    \n    def extract_expiration_date(self, text):\n        \"\"\"Find and parse expiration dates\"\"\"\n        # Common date patterns\n        date_patterns = [\n            r'EXP[IRATION]*[:\\s]+(\\d{1,2}[-/]\\d{1,2}[-/]\\d{2,4})',\n            r'EXPIRES[:\\s]+(\\d{1,2}[-/]\\d{1,2}[-/]\\d{2,4})',\n            r'VALID[:\\s]+UNTIL[:\\s]+(\\d{1,2}[-/]\\d{1,2}[-/]\\d{2,4})',\n            r'(\\d{1,2}[-/]\\d{1,2}[-/]\\d{2,4})',\n        ]\n        \n        for pattern in date_patterns:\n            match = re.search(pattern, text, re.IGNORECASE)\n            if match:\n                date_str = match.group(1)\n                return self.parse_date(date_str)\n        \n        return None\n    \n    def parse_date(self, date_str):\n        \"\"\"Parse various date formats\"\"\"\n        formats = [\n            '%m/%d/%Y', '%m-%d-%Y', '%m/%d/%y', '%m-%d-%y',\n            '%d/%m/%Y', '%d-%m-%Y', '%Y-%m-%d', '%Y/%m/%d'\n        ]\n        \n        for fmt in formats:\n            try:\n                return datetime.strptime(date_str, fmt)\n            except ValueError:\n                continue\n        \n        return None\n    \n    def is_date_valid(self, expiration_date):\n        \"\"\"Check if document is still valid\"\"\"\n        if expiration_date is None:\n            return True  # Some documents don't expire (DD214)\n        \n        return expiration_date > datetime.now()\n    \n    def match_names(self, account_name, document_names):\n        \"\"\"Fuzzy match account holder name with document names\"\"\"\n        # Normalize account name\n        account_name_clean = self.normalize_name(account_name)\n        \n        best_match_score = 0\n        best_match_name = None\n        \n        for doc_name in document_names:\n            doc_name_clean = self.normalize_name(doc_name)\n            \n            # Use multiple fuzzy matching algorithms\n            ratio = fuzz.ratio(account_name_clean, doc_name_clean)\n            partial_ratio = fuzz.partial_ratio(account_name_clean, doc_name_clean)\n            token_sort = fuzz.token_sort_ratio(account_name_clean, doc_name_clean)\n            \n            # Take the highest score\n            score = max(ratio, partial_ratio, token_sort)\n            \n            if score > best_match_score:\n                best_match_score = score\n                best_match_name = doc_name\n        \n        return {\n            'match_score': best_match_score,\n            'matched_name': best_match_name,\n            'is_match': best_match_score >= self.confidence_threshold\n        }\n    \n    def normalize_name(self, name):\n        \"\"\"Clean and normalize names for comparison\"\"\"\n        # Remove extra spaces, convert to uppercase\n        name = ' '.join(name.upper().split())\n        \n        # Remove common suffixes\n        suffixes = ['JR', 'SR', 'II', 'III', 'IV']\n        for suffix in suffixes:\n            name = name.replace(f' {suffix}', '')\n        \n        # Remove punctuation\n        name = re.sub(r'[^\\w\\s]', '', name)\n        \n        return name\n    \n    def verify_document(self, image_path, account_holder_name):\n        \"\"\"Main verification logic\"\"\"\n        result = {\n            'verified': False,\n            'confidence': 0,\n            'document_type': None,\n            'expiration_valid': False,\n            'name_match': None,\n            'reason': None,\n            'extracted_text': None\n        }\n        \n        try:\n            # Extract text\n            text = self.extract_text_from_image(image_path)\n            result['extracted_text'] = text\n            \n            # Classify document\n            doc_type = self.classify_document_type(text)\n            result['document_type'] = doc_type\n            \n            if doc_type == 'UNKNOWN':\n                result['reason'] = 'Document type not recognized'\n                return result\n            \n            # Extract names\n            document_names = self.extract_name_from_document(text, doc_type)\n            \n            if not document_names:\n                result['reason'] = 'Could not extract name from document'\n                return result\n            \n            # Match names\n            name_match = self.match_names(account_holder_name, document_names)\n            result['name_match'] = name_match\n            \n            if not name_match['is_match']:\n                result['reason'] = f\"Name mismatch (confidence: {name_match['match_score']}%)\"\n                return result\n            \n            # Check expiration\n            expiration_date = self.extract_expiration_date(text)\n            is_valid = self.is_date_valid(expiration_date)\n            result['expiration_valid'] = is_valid\n            \n            if expiration_date and not is_valid:\n                result['reason'] = 'Document has expired'\n                return result\n            \n            # Success!\n            result['verified'] = True\n            result['confidence'] = name_match['match_score']\n            result['reason'] = 'Successfully verified'\n            \n        except Exception as e:\n            result['reason'] = f'Processing error: {str(e)}'\n        \n        return result\n\n\n# API Endpoint\nbot = MilitaryVerificationBot()\n\n@app.route('/verify/military', methods=['POST'])\ndef verify_military_status():\n    if 'document' not in request.files:\n        return jsonify({'error': 'No document uploaded'}), 400\n    \n    file = request.files['document']\n    account_holder = request.form.get('account_holder')\n    account_number = request.form.get('account_number')\n    \n    if not account_holder:\n        return jsonify({'error': 'Account holder name required'}), 400\n    \n    # Save file temporarily\n    filename = secure_filename(file.filename)\n    filepath = os.path.join('/tmp', filename)\n    file.save(filepath)\n    \n    # Verify document\n    result = bot.verify_document(filepath, account_holder)\n    \n    # Clean up\n    os.remove(filepath)\n    \n    # If verified, update database\n    if result['verified']:\n        # TODO: Update customer account in database\n        # update_customer_military_status(account_number, True)\n        \n        return jsonify({\n            'status': 'verified',\n            'verified': True,\n            'confidence': result['confidence'],\n            'document_type': result['document_type'],\n            'message': 'Thank you for your service! Your military discount has been applied.',\n            'next_steps': {\n                'credit_applied': True,\n                'monthly_discount': '$10.00'\n            }\n        })\n    else:\n        # Failed verification - provide escalation path\n        return jsonify({\n            'status': 'needs_review',\n            'verified': False,\n            'reason': result['reason'],\n            'confidence': result.get('confidence', 0),\n            'document_type': result['document_type'],\n            'message': 'We need a bit more information to verify your military status.',\n            'next_steps': {\n                'options': [\n                    {\n                        'action': 'retry',\n                        'label': 'Try uploading a different document',\n                        'description': 'Make sure the document is clear and all text is readable'\n                    },\n                    {\n                        'action': 'contact_support',\n                        'label': 'Speak with a representative',\n                        'phone': '1-800-FRONTIER',\n                        'chat_available': True\n                    }\n                ]\n            }\n        })\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    app.run(debug=True)\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Step 3: Contact Support Card (Fallback UI)**\n\n```python\n# React Native Component for Failed Verification\nconst SupportContactCard = ({ verificationResult }) => {\n  return (\n    <View style={styles.supportCard}>\n      <View style={styles.iconContainer}>\n        <Text style={styles.icon}>üéñÔ∏è</Text>\n      </View>\n      \n      <Text style={styles.title}>\n        We're Here to Help\n      </Text>\n      \n      <Text style={styles.message}>\n        We couldn't automatically verify your military status, but our team is \n        ready to assist you.\n      </Text>\n      \n      <Text style={styles.reason}>\n        Reason: {verificationResult.reason}\n      </Text>\n      \n      <View style={styles.optionsContainer}>\n        <TouchableOpacity \n          style={styles.retryButton}\n          onPress={() => navigation.goBack()}\n        >\n          <Text style={styles.retryText}>üì∏ Try Another Document</Text>\n        </TouchableOpacity>\n        \n        <TouchableOpacity \n          style={styles.callButton}\n          onPress={() => Linking.openURL('tel:18003772000')}\n        >\n          <Text style={styles.callText}>üìû Call Support</Text>\n          <Text style={styles.phoneNumber}>1-800-377-2000</Text>\n        </TouchableOpacity>\n        \n        <TouchableOpacity \n          style={styles.chatButton}\n          onPress={() => openLiveChat()}\n        >\n          <Text style={styles.chatText}>üí¨ Live Chat Support</Text>\n        </TouchableOpacity>\n        \n        <TouchableOpacity \n          style={styles.emailButton}\n          onPress={() => openEmailForm()}\n        >\n          <Text style={styles.emailText}>‚úâÔ∏è Email Documents</Text>\n        </TouchableOpacity>\n      </View>\n      \n      <View style={styles.tipsContainer}>\n        <Text style={styles.tipsTitle}>Tips for Better Results:</Text>\n        <Text style={styles.tip}>‚Ä¢ Ensure document is well-lit and in focus</Text>\n        <Text style={styles.tip}>‚Ä¢ Capture all corners of the ID</Text>\n        <Text style={styles.tip}>‚Ä¢ Avoid glare or shadows</Text>\n        <Text style={styles.tip}>‚Ä¢ Make sure text is readable</Text>\n      </View>\n    </View>\n  );\n};\n```\n\n---\n\n## üé® **Sample Training Data**\n\n### **Document Type Recognition Training**\n\n```python\n# training_data.py\nMILITARY_DOCUMENT_PATTERNS = {\n    'CAC': {\n        'keywords': [\n            'COMMON ACCESS CARD',\n            'DEPARTMENT OF DEFENSE',\n            'CAC',\n            'DOD ID',\n            'ARMED FORCES',\n            'ACTIVE DUTY'\n        ],\n        'layout_features': {\n            'has_photo': True,\n            'has_chip': True,\n            'has_barcode': True,\n            'text_density': 'high'\n        }\n    },\n    'DD214': {\n        'keywords': [\n            'DD FORM 214',\n            'CERTIFICATE OF RELEASE',\n            'DISCHARGE FROM ACTIVE DUTY',\n            'MEMBER 4',\n            'CHARACTER OF SERVICE',\n            'SEPARATION CODE'\n        ],\n        'layout_features': {\n            'has_photo': False,\n            'is_form': True,\n            'has_sections': True\n        }\n    },\n    'VHIC': {\n        'keywords': [\n            'VETERAN HEALTH',\n            'VHIC',\n            'VETERANS HEALTH IDENTIFICATION',\n            'VA',\n            'DEPARTMENT OF VETERANS AFFAIRS'\n        ],\n        'layout_features': {\n            'has_photo': True,\n            'has_barcode': True\n        }\n    }\n}\n\n# Example names for testing fuzzy matching\nTEST_CASES = [\n    {\n        'account_name': 'John Smith',\n        'document_name': 'SMITH, JOHN A',\n        'should_match': True\n    },\n    {\n        'account_name': 'Mary Johnson',\n        'document_name': 'JOHNSON MARY ELIZABETH',\n        'should_match': True\n    },\n    {\n        'account_name': 'Robert Williams Jr',\n        'document_name': 'WILLIAMS, ROBERT JR',\n        'should_match': True\n    },\n    {\n        'account_name': 'Jennifer Davis',\n        'document_name': 'DAVIS JENNIFER MARIE',\n        'should_match': True\n    }\n]\n```\n\n---\n\n## üìä **Success Metrics Dashboard**\n\n```python\n# dashboard.py - Analytics for hackathon demo\nclass VerificationMetrics:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.total_attempts = 0\n        self.successful_verifications = 0\n        self.failed_verifications = 0\n        self.manual_escalations = 0\n        self.average_processing_time = 0\n        \n    def get_success_rate(self):\n        if self.total_attempts == 0:\n            return 0\n        return (self.successful_verifications / self.total_attempts) * 100\n    \n    def get_dashboard_data(self):\n        return {\n            'total_attempts': self.total_attempts,\n            'success_rate': f\"{self.get_success_rate():.1f}%\",\n            'auto_verified': self.successful_verifications,\n            'manual_review': self.manual_escalations,\n            'avg_time': f\"{self.average_processing_time:.2f}s\",\n            'top_document_types': {\n                'DD214': 45,\n                'CAC': 30,\n                'VHIC': 15,\n                'Other': 10\n            }\n        }\n```\n\n---\n\n## üöÄ **Quick Start for Hackathon**\n\n### **Installation**\n\n```bash\n# Backend setup\npip install flask pytesseract opencv-python pillow fuzzywuzzy python-rapidfuzz\npip install python-Levenshtein  # For faster fuzzy matching\n\n# Install Tesseract OCR\n# MacOS: brew install tesseract\n# Ubuntu: sudo apt-get install tesseract-ocr\n# Windows: Download from GitHub\n\n# Frontend (if building React Native)\nnpm install react-native-document-picker\nnpm install react-native-image-crop-picker\n```\n\n### **Quick Test**\n\n```python\n# test_verification.py\nfrom app import MilitaryVerificationBot\n\nbot = MilitaryVerificationBot()\n\n# Test with sample image\nresult = bot.verify_document(\n    'sample_cac.jpg',\n    'Justin Moosetown'\n)\n\nprin